From the acclaimed director of 'Waltz with Bashir', one of Ari Folman's earlier movies.

Plot: Agon Schultz, the last Nazi in the worls, is being turned over to Israel through an Israeli-Syrian peace treaty. Schultz is scheduled to be trialed in Jerusalem for his part in the transport of Jews throughout the world. While Schultz is at the border cross in Ramat haGolan, Dani Hoffman, a rich businessman and son to Holocaust survivors, issues a two million dollar contract on the Nazi's head. Hoffman recruits two teams - Perach and Tiktak, and Dodo and Vitalik - and orders them to bring Schultz unharmed to the highest mountain in the country. There, at the top of the snow covered summit, he intends to shoot the last Nazi himself.

Made in Israel is a story of five Israelis: A trumpet player, two debts collectors, and a couple of Russian hitmen, unwillingly turned Nazi hunters. They Wander snowy Ramat haGolan, in heavy fog, with an 82 year old Nazi they have to look after life a baby, so he can reach the mountain safely. Or the money's gone.
